metadata.name: Travelling Gondola #68
metadata.description:
The Traveler says:

-Each planet has a story, in this gondola you can talk to the stars, confess to the moon... I've seen the beginning and end of ages, slowly... slowly I travel and witness the passage of everything, I'm in no hurry if time is slower than me, and one day we will reach the singularity.

Is it the end?

-

Interactivity:

[ARROW UP] - Ticket Up.
[ARROW DOWN] - Ticket Down.
[MOUSE HOVER ON TICKET] - Shows what each feature defines.

[A] - Render a 20 frames gif.
[S] - Render a 40 frames gif.
[D] - Render a 60 frames gif.
 
[Z] - Save a printscreen of canvas.
[X] - Up/Down ballons.
[C] - Open/Close blueprint.

-

Travelling Gondola have 7 Features:
-Gunwale
-Hull Sides
-Hull Middle
-Biome
-Superficie
-Vegetation
-Atmosphere



by Gen Doodler | twitter.com/GenDoodler

metadata.name: INTERFERENCES #203
metadata.description:
INTERFERENCES is an abstract representation of the incredible collaboration between artists, collectors and developers on fxhash.

Each edition is composed of a multitude of lines representing each individual on the platform. The color of each line defines the role of each individual in this universe. Through their interactions, and the interferences they produce, each line participates in the creation of a common work.

Happy birthday fxhash! And congratulations to all those who work for its success.

Primary sales are donated to the Processing Foundation

[TOUCHSCREEN]
* Double Tap to save the current image

[KEYBOARD]
* Press [S] to save the current image
* Press [1] to save a 1500x2000 pixels PNG
* Press [2] to save a 3000x4000 pixels PNG
* Press [3] to save a 6000x8000 pixels PNG
* Press [0] to save 3 individual SVG for each color set of lines + the background image PNG
* Press [9] to save a grouped SVG of all the lines + the background image PNG

Artist: Estienne
Nov. 2022
NFT License 2.0

Credits to Piter Pasma (@piterpasma) for the Reumann-Witkam line simplification algorithm used in this generator

metadata.name: codeTurning 3: (un)patterning #167
metadata.description:
The codeTurning project aims to reflect my journey from traditional tools to code, in which any day I learn a new skill.
Join me towards something new for me. Something different from the previous.
Sometimes we will stand on the shoulders of giants.

Let's explore and see how far we get.

Lesson 3: (un)patterning

In this lesson I wanted to play at making patterns but also at breaking patterns, finding, in the end, as much beauty in order as in disorder. I would like to dedicate this project to all those people who break out of the pattern, who don't fit into the pre-established grid and who look for their own space.

metadata.name: Undulated #76
metadata.description:
Undulated is an exploration of flow fields consisting of trigonometric functions. In each piece, thousands of particles move according to the flow described by the flow field. This results in natural and soft-looking esthetics, which seem to resemble spiralling galaxies, meandering rivers, rolling hills, carved canyons or even firing neurons! Don't forget to look at the animation as it is really soothing! 

In live view, the resolution can be changed by adding &res=... to the URL!

Created by MathBird using p5js

zancannabis is a celebration of 4/20 2023 and is of course a respectful parody of the artwork from the legend that is zancan.

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #773
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan
